# Portfolio Website - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a React-based portfolio website showcasing software engineering and art projects. Built with React 18 and JavaScript (not TypeScript).

## Code Style & Formatting

### General
- Use JavaScript (JSX), NOT TypeScript
- Follow Prettier configuration (single quotes, 140 char line length, 2-space tabs)
- Run `yarn format` before committing changes
- Use named exports for components: `export function ComponentName() {}`
- Use arrow functions for inline/small functions

### Imports
- Use absolute imports from `src` directory (configured in jsconfig.json)
- Import order (handled by Prettier plugin):
  1. External packages (React, libraries)
  2. Internal components (`components/...`)
  3. Assets (`assets/...`)
  4. Data (`data/...`)
  5. Styles (`styles/...`)
- Example:
  ```jsx
  import React from 'react';
  import { ComponentName } from 'components/Path/ComponentName';
  import ImageAsset from 'assets/path/image.svg';
  import 'styles/Path/ComponentName.css';
  ```

## Component Structure

### Component Files
- Place components in appropriate folders under `src/components/`
- Use PascalCase for component names
- Named exports: `export function MyComponent() {}`
- Each major component should have its own folder
- Co-locate CSS files with components in `src/styles/` following the same folder structure

### Component Organization
```
src/
  components/
    MyComponent/
      MyComponent.jsx
      SubComponent.jsx (if needed)
  styles/
    MyComponent/
      MyComponent.css
```

### Functional Components
- Use functional components with hooks (no class components)
- Destructure props in function signature when appropriate
- Use React hooks (useState, useEffect, etc.) as needed

## Styling

### CSS
- Use plain CSS (not CSS-in-JS, not Tailwind)
- One CSS file per component in `src/styles/`
- Use semantic class names and IDs
- Follow BEM-like naming when appropriate
- Use CSS variables defined in `Globals.css` for colors and common values
- Import animate.css classes where needed for animations

### Responsive Design
- Design mobile-first
- Use media queries for responsive layouts
- Test on multiple screen sizes

## Data Management

### Content Data
- Store content data in `src/data/` folder
- Keep data separate from components for easy updates
- Use clear, exported constants and arrays
- Examples:
  - `experiences.js` - work experience data
  - `swProjects.js` - software projects
  - `technologies.js` - tech stack icons and info
  - `colors.js` - color constants

### Data Structure
- Export named constants for reusability
- Use descriptive property names
- Include all necessary metadata (company, duration, technologies, etc.)

## Assets

### Organization
- Store all assets in `src/assets/`
- Organize by type:
  - `Company_Logos/` - company/brand logos
  - `Dev_Icons/` - technology icons
  - `Illustrations/` - custom illustrations
  - `Organic_Shapes/` - decorative shapes/blobs
  - `Projects/` - project screenshots/media
- Use optimized formats (SVG for logos/icons, WebP for images)

### Asset Usage
- Import assets directly in components
- Use descriptive alt text for images
- Optimize images before adding to project

## Features & Libraries

### Key Dependencies
- `react-animate-on-scroll` - for scroll animations
- `animate.css` - CSS animation library
- `swiper` - for carousels/sliders
- `html-react-parser` - for parsing HTML strings
- `react-inlinesvg` - for inline SVG manipulation

### Animation
- Use `ScrollAnimation` component from react-animate-on-scroll
- Include `animateOnce` prop to prevent re-animation
- Use animate.css classes for animation effects

## Development Practices

### Before Committing
- Run `yarn format` to format code
- Test locally with `yarn start`
- Check for console errors and warnings
- Verify responsive design

### Adding New Features
- Create components in appropriate folders
- Add corresponding CSS files in `styles/`
- Update data files if adding new content
- Import and use in `App.jsx` or parent component
- Test all functionality

### Performance
- Use WebP for images when possible
- Lazy load images and components where appropriate
- Minimize bundle size
- Optimize assets before adding

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `AboutMe.jsx`)
- Data files: camelCase (e.g., `experiences.js`)
- CSS files: PascalCase matching component (e.g., `AboutMe.css`)
- Assets: snake_case or PascalCase (e.g., `Profile_Pic.webp`, `IntuitLogo.svg`)

## Common Patterns

### Section Components
- Each page section is a component (AboutMe, Experience, etc.)
- Use semantic HTML5 tags (`<section>`, `<article>`, etc.)
- Include unique IDs for navigation/scrolling
- Wrap in containers with `page-container` class

### Navigation
- Use IDs for scroll-to sections
- Navbar links to section IDs
- Include ScrollToTopButton component

## Testing
- Run `yarn start` and manually test in browser
- Check responsive design at various breakpoints
- Test all interactive elements
- Verify animations work as expected

## Deployment
- Deployed via GitHub Pages
- Run `yarn deploy` to build and deploy
- Updates to main branch should be production-ready

